==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Middle English]] "me thinketh" (‘seems to me’) < Old English "me thyncth". In [[Early Modern English]], used at least 150 times by William Shakespeare; in [[Middle English]] by writer Geoffrey Chaucer, "me thinketh"; and in [[Old English]] by the Beowulf poet, "me thincth."

===Verb===
'''methinks'''

# {{archaic}} It [[seem]]s to me.

